{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/how-i-created-a-real-time-twitter-sentiment-analysis-tool-for-covid-292ff6a6323b", "time": 1683005874.654679, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/how-i-created-a-real-time-twitter-sentiment-analysis-tool-for-covid-292ff6a6323b/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "How I created a Real-Time Twitter Sentiment Analysis tool for COVID | by Dimitris Effrosynidis | Towards Data Science", "h1": "How I created a Real-Time Twitter Sentiment Analysis tool for COVID", "description": "Using Machine Learning and Python, I developed a model to classify tweets about COVID into positive, negative or neutral."}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "http://alt.qcri.org/semeval2017/task4/", "anchor_text": "Sem-eval", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://github.com/Deffro/text-preprocessing-techniques", "anchor_text": "16 pre-processing techniques", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://t.co/SEpa9yxg87", "anchor_text": "https://t.co/SEpa9yxg87", "paragraph_index": 5}], "all_paragraphs": ["Twitter is the most successful microblogging service with 150 million daily users. 6.000 tweets are written every second. People tweet about everything that comes in mind and use hashtags to associate the tweet with a topic.", "We can build a machine learning classifier to rate tweets based on their Sentiment. A tweet can express a positive, negative, or neutral Sentiment.", "I will create a simple model to classify such tweets in real-time and create a graph for the overall Sentiment of COVID. What\u2019s the people\u2019s sentiment about the virus?", "First, I need a dataset of tweets that are already classified into one of the three categories to train my model. Sem-eval provides a relatively big dataset of 65.854 already labeled tweets. As there is no COVID-specific twitter dataset, I will use a general twitter dataset.", "Next, I will pre-process the tweets using combinations of 16 pre-processing techniques. The initial form of a tweet is not in a suitable form for natural language processing (NLP). Tweets are not clean, contain URLs, user mentions, slang, abbreviations, numbers, repetitive punctuation, elongated words, etc.Thus a text like this:", "Stay Home!! Stay Safe!! Stay Happy!! Stay Alive. We can Fight with COVID-19 #stayhomestaysafe #stayhealthy \u2026 https://t.co/SEpa9yxg87", "Stay Home multiExclamation Stay Safe multiExclamation Stay Happy multiExclamation Stay Alive. We can Fight with COVID- stayhomestaysafe stayhealthy url", "I trained 10 machine learning models on the pre-processed dataset. I chose not to use deep learning models (like BERT) as I am no expert. So, I used models like Logistic Regression, Naive Bayes, K-Nearest Neighbors, Random Forest, and Support Vector Machines. The latter outperformed the rest in performance (f-measure) and I chose it.", "A train-test split was performed (20% test). The TF-IDF Vectorizer transformed the text token to numbers, stop words were not removed and the performance metrics of the classification are shown below.", "I chose the Linear SVC and retrained the model on the whole data. I remember back in the day that SVMs were state of the art for NLP! The trained model was saved in a pickle.", "In order to get tweets in real-time, I need to have an account and get an api key. Next, I can pick keywords and only tweets containing these keywords will be returned. I chose \u201ccovid\u201d as a keyword.", "When a new tweet from the stream of tweets is acquired, the trained model is predicting its sentiment and saves the tweet in a text file.", "At the same time, a script is running that plots the contents of this text file in real-time as more data are added to it. It uses matplotlib\u2019s animation capabilities to refresh the plot. If the tweet is positive, the y-axis gets +1, if negative -1 and for neutral +0.", "As can be seen, after 1.000 tweets about COVID, the overall sentiment is -80.", "The same real-time plot can be generated for any keywords and the scripts can run 24/7 to collect and label tweets.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F292ff6a6323b&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fhow-i-created-a-real-time-twitter-sentiment-analysis-tool-for-covid-292ff6a6323b&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fhow-i-created-a-real-time-twitter-sentiment-analysis-tool-for-covid-292ff6a6323b&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fhow-i-created-a-real-time-twitter-sentiment-analysis-tool-for-covid-292ff6a6323b&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fhow-i-created-a-real-time-twitter-sentiment-analysis-tool-for-covid-292ff6a6323b&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------